#   SUBS: submodule-recursion tickets

Audit of `be`'s submodule recursion across all verbs (2026-06-05).  Model
and spec in [Submodules].  Recursion is **default-on for every source type**
(git/ssh included); `--sub` is a dead no-op, `--nosub` is the only opt-out
(verified: no `CLIHas(c,"--sub")` anywhere, six `--nosub` sites in
`beagle/BE.cli.c`).  HEAD, GET (checkout/clone/force/prune), and POST
topology (post-order, synthetic dot-branch `?/<sub>/.<parent>/<branch>`,
gitlink bumps, detached-refuse) all work.  The gaps below are the deltas.

| Ticket | Sev | Verb | One-line |
|--------|-----|------|----------|
| [SUBS-001] | HIGH (LANDED `97de77b8`) | post | a level's own tracked edits silently dropped when that level also has a dirty sub (selective-mode flip from the recursion's gitlink-bump put-row) вЂ” fixed via option (a): `sniff/POST.c` `post_pd_cb` no longer flips `any_pd` on sub-bump put rows |
| [SUBS-002] | HIGH (LANDED `a31bdfcf`) | patch | unusable on any gitlink-bearing parent вЂ” fixed: `BE_PLAN_PATCH` no longer excludes `BEActSubsPatch` on transport URIs (maskв†’0, `beagle/DISPATCH.c`); spurious `bad ref ''` silenced; patch/28+29 added |
| [SUBS-003] | MED (FIXED) | get | clone status report stamped `DDMon` not `HH:MM` (mktime DST round-trip); broke get/05,07 вЂ” fixed in `dog/HUNK.c` |
| [SUBS-004] | MED (LANDED `5fb56d6f`) | put | bare `be put` with only the sub dirty exited 206/PUTNONE вЂ” fixed: `be_recurse_capture` propagates a child `*NONE` as the NONE class (no longer collapsed to OK) and `BEActSubsRelay` returns `BESTOP` (в†’OK) when a sub staged work, clearing the parent's stale PUTNONE; a truly-empty bare put still surfaces PUTNONE |
| [SUBS-005] | MED (LANDED `9aabd863`) | delete | path-scoped delete of a sub / sub-interior file false-positived DELDIRTY вЂ” fixed: `sniff/DEL.c` `del_sub_classify` recognises gitlink + sub-interior paths and skips with a sub-aware message instead of DELDIRTY (full unmount deferred to [SUBS-008]) |
| [SUBS-006] | MED (LANDED `414d9f96`) | post | git-remote push aborts NOBRANCH on a clean nested sub whose synthetic branch does not yet exist вЂ” fixed: detached wt returns POSTNONE (no-op) from POSTPromote's missing-branch arm (`sniff/POST.c`); post/29 added |
| [SUBS-007] | MED (LANDED `3ab50efd`) | head | `be head` omits sub working-tree dirty state (spec L20); head/04 is a false-positive test вЂ” fixed: `behead_recurse_cb` now relays each sub's bare status (`beagle/BE.cli.c`); head/21 added, head/04 tightened |
| [SUBS-008] | LOW (LANDED `50722656`) | get | gitlink-removed target unmounts the `.be` anchor but orphans the sub's worktree files on disk вЂ” fixed: `BEGetSubUnmount` FILErmrf's the whole mount dir (`beagle/SUBS.c`); be-get-sub-unmount-clean added |
| [SUBS-009] | LOW (PARTLY LANDED `50724d9a`) | put | sub-add via `be put` вЂ” fixed the misleading PUTNONE with an actionable refusal naming the `sniff sub-mount` step (`sniff/PUT.c`); full git-submodule-add parity (URL+pin) в†’ [SUBS-013]. put/11 added |
| [SUBS-010] | LOW (LANDED `cda5c691`) | docs | stale "git source needs `--sub`" comments/shim (`test/lib/submodules.sh`, get/05,07) describe removed gating вЂ” fixed: shim dropped, phase-2 narrative purged, tests now drive default recursion |
| [SUBS-011] | HIGH (LANDED `7d37f90f`) | grep/spot/regex | search projectors don't descend into subs вЂ” fixed: index-on-mount (`BEIndexMount`) + `BEProjectorSubs` recursion (`beagle/SUBS.c`,`BE.cli.c`); spot/10 added |
| [SUBS-012] | MED (LANDED `7d37f90f`) | diff/tree/blob/refs/log/blame | projectors parent-only at a gitlink вЂ” fixed: whole-tree fan-out (diff:/tree:) + path-in-mount routing (blob:/tree:/log:/blame:); diff/06, tree/01 added. `refs:?**` deferred (refs: unimplemented in keeper) |
| [SUBS-013] | LOW | put | full `git submodule add` parity: stage a new `160000` gitlink + `.gitmodules` from `be put` вЂ” needs a chosen URL source + pin grammar (escalated from SUBS-009) |
| [SUBS-014] | LOW | put | misleading "does not exist вЂ” skipped" PUTNONE fires for ANY plain untracked dir named without a trailing slash (not sub-specific); wants a "did you mean `dir/`?" hint |
| [SUBS-015] | LOW | blob | `blob:<path>` WITHOUT `?ref` returns KEEPNONE even in the parent (pre-existing, not sub-related) |

Tests added this audit: `test/put/08-10`, `test/delete/07-09`, `test/patch/28-29`,
`test/post/26-27`, `test/head/21`, `test/all/01-subs-all-verbs` (bug repros
registered `WILL_FAIL` until the owning ticket lands).  `test/post/26-27`
landed green with SUBS-001 (`97de77b8`) and are off `WILL_FAIL`.  `test/put/09`
landed green with SUBS-004 (`5fb56d6f`) and `test/delete/08` with SUBS-005
(`9aabd863`).  The rest stay `WILL_FAIL` pending their tickets.

